This paper deals with the expressive power of Higher-Order Modal Fixpoint Logic (HFL), which is a topic in logic and theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also involves automata theory and formal languages, which are covered in cs.LMCS (Logical Methods in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper's use of parity automata and the Banach Fixpoint Theorem suggests a connection to cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Finally, the paper's focus on expressive power and hierarchy suggests a connection to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
